-- HSBC Bank Middle East Said to Plan Sale of $500 Million in Five-Year Bonds
-- B y   H a r i s   A n w a r
-- 2010-10-14T12:06:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/hsbc-bank-middle-east-said-to-plan-sale-of-500-million-in-five-year-bonds.html
HSBC Bank Middle East Ltd. plans to
sell $500 million of five-year bonds that may be priced to yield
about 175 basis points more than the benchmark mid-swap rate,
according to a person with knowledge of the sale.  HSBC Holdings Plc is managing the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Haris Anwar in Dubai at 
